<ul>
<li>Platform manual converted from DocBook to Markdown to improve readability and enhance contribution.</li>
<li>Extensive additions to the platform documentation.</li>
<li>Easier query construction with JDatabaseQuery::format</li>
<li>Support for composite keys in JTable</li>
<li>Improvements to the JGitHub API</li>
<li>Improvements to JLog around excluding categories and features for syslog</li>
<li>Improved Windows support for testing and building</li>
<li>PHPMailer updated to 5.2.2</li>
</ul>
<p>The full list of commits is available here <a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-platform/commits/12.3">https://github.com/joomla/joomla-platform/commits/12.3</a> and the api doc here <a href="http://api.joomla.org/">http://api.joomla.org</a>. The Joomla! Platform Manual is available at <a href="http://joomla.github.com/joomla-platform/">http://joomla.github.com/joomla-platform/</a>.</p>
<h2>Project size</h2>
<ul>
<li>Classes: 305 (300 in platform 12.2)</li>
<li>Methods: 2187 (2136 in platform 12.2)</li>
</ul>
<h2>Summary of code quality</h2>
<ul>
<li>Check style: 123 warnings (124 in platform 12.2)</li>
<li><a href="http://developer.joomla.org/coverage/">Test Coverage</a>: 39.4% (38.16% in platform 12.2).</li>
</ul>
